# Wateray Baseline (Mandatory)

- Keep module boundaries explicit: UI in `ElectronApp/`, runtime engine in `core/`, automation in `scripts/`, docs in `docs/`.
- Keep process boundaries explicit: `ElectronApp/` is frontend console; `core/cmd/waterayd` is backend daemon.
- Keep core daemon as the runtime authority for subscriptions, groups, routing, connection stage, stats, and runtime config.
- Keep UI independent from core lifetime: closing UI must not stop backend runtime.
- Keep user-facing text centralized in frontend locale/resources; avoid scattered hard-coded product text.
- Keep tunnel/routing related changes verifiable; include runnable verification steps in the same change.
- If rules conflict, prioritize architecture/runtime boundary rules first, then language/framework-specific rules.

## Example

```text
BAD: Move subscription parsing and runtime decisions into React page handlers.
GOOD: Keep runtime logic in core; Electron frontend only sends commands and renders snapshots.
```
